	<div id="text_about">
	<h1>About me</h1>
	<p>I was born in 1978 at Tainan City, a peaceful and conservative city in southern Taiwan. My father was a high school mathematics teacher and my mother was a music teacher. Since my parents were both teachers, they imposed strict discipline on me. I studied very hard in my childhood and teenage.</p>
	<p>Finally, I got admission from <a href="http://www.ntu.edu.tw/english/" target="_blank">National Taiwan University</a>, the best college in my country. The electronic industry in Taiwan was promising and offered best career opportunities at that time so I decided to major in Electrical Engineering. During my undergraduate study, my favorite subject was electronics and microcontroller. I liked building devices such as digital clocks and toys.</p>
	<p>After my graduation, I worked as an IC designer in <a href="http://www.holtek.com/English/default.htm" target="_blank">Holtek Semiconductor Inc.</a>, where I did much hard work in labs. Later I worked as a field application engineer in <a href="http://www.magellandiscovery.com/index.php" target="_blank">Magellan Discovery Corporation</a>, where my social skill was improved through negotiation with clients. Gradually I found my passion in coding and I made up my mind to become a programmer. Then I started saving money for my future study.</p>
	<p>First I came to study in Computer Science department of <a href="http://www.callutheran.edu/schools/cas/programs/mscs/" target="_blank">California Lutheran University</a>. Later I transferred to <a href="http://www.cs.usc.edu/" target="_blank">University of Southern California</a>, here I really enjoy my study. So far I am especially fond of computer graphics, gaming, and multimedia. Hopefully I could find related job in the future.</p>
	<p>Since my wife and I came to US in 2008, we have visited many places around this country. US is a diverse country and also has plenty of natural scenes. We like here so much that we decided to stay after I complete my study. We believe this is the right place for us. Therefore, I started preparing for future career in US.</p>	
	</div>

